# Web React Rules

## API client

All HTTP goes through `src/api/client.ts`:

- Base URL: `import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL` (must include `/api`, e.g. `http://localhost:8080/api`)
- Paths are servlet-relative: `/auth/login`, `/posts`, `/users`
- Auth header: `Authorization: Bearer ${token}` via `apiFetch(..., { token })`

## Authentication

- Login/register return `{ token }` only
- User profile parsed from JWT via `parseUserFromToken(token)`
- Full profile refresh: `getMe(token)` → `GET /auth/me`
- State: `AuthContext` — `hasRole`, `hasScope`, `hasAnyRole`
- UI gates: `RoleGate`, `ProtectedRoute`

Do not expect a `user` object in login/register responses.

## Components

- Functional components + hooks
- Colocate page components in `src/pages/`
- Post images: `postImageUrl()` from client (resolves against `VITE_API_URL`)
- List → detail navigation: see `.cursor/rules/web-navigation.mdc` (`BackLink`, `PageBackLink`, `listItemBackState`)
- Themes: `ThemeProvider` + `ThemeToggle` in nav. Use CSS variables from `index.css` (`--card-bg`, `--flame-glow`, etc.); themes are `ember` (dark) and `steam` (light). Never hardcode colors in page CSS.

## Examples

```typescript
// BAD — duplicate fetch logic
const res = await fetch(`${API_URL}/api/posts`, { headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${t}` } })

// GOOD
await apiFetch('/posts', { token })
```

```tsx
// BAD — role string check scattered in JSX
{user?.role === 'ADMIN' && <AdminPanel />}

// GOOD — scope-aware gate
<RoleGate scope="users:read">
  <AdminPanel />
</RoleGate>
```

Reference: `docs/architecture.md`, `.env.example`.
